@node "Listview" "Available commodities"
@toc "Fenster"

    Available commodities

    This list shows all running commodities in the system.
    Only the commodities marked with an "*" will be removed,
    if you select "Remove all" (and the option is set).

    You can use the cursor keys to scroll through the list.
    [RETURN] will open the interface window (if possible)
    and [DEL] will remove the selected commodity from the
    system.

@endnode
@node "Information"
@toc "Fenster"

    Information

    Shows the title and the description of the selected
    commodity.

@endnode

@node "ShowInterface"
@toc "Fenster"

    Show interface

    Pops up the interface window of the selected commodity.

@endnode

@node "HideInterface"
@toc "Fenster"

    Hide interface

    Closes the window of the selected commodity.

@endnode

@node "Aktive" "Aktiv/Inaktiv"
@toc "Fenster"

    Active/Inactive

    Tells you, if the selected commodity is enabled or not.
    You can change its state by clicking on this cycle
    gadget.

@endnode

@node "Remove"
@toc "Fenster"

    Remove

    Removes the selected commodity from the system (if you
    selected "Exchange", CX will quit).

@endnode

@node "AktiveAll"
@toc "Fenster"

    Disable all / Enable all

    Use the cycle gadget to disable (or enable) all shown
    commodities.

@endnode

@node "RemoveAll" "Remove all"
@toc "Fenster"
@next "Listview"

    Remove all

    If you click on this button all commodities will be
    removed.

    If option "remove * only" is set, only the marked
    commodities will be removed.

    If option "Requester" is set, a requester will appear.

@endnode

@node "Verbergen" "Hide"
@toc "Menu"
@next "Quit"
@prev "About"

    Hide

    Closes CX's window. You must press the hot key to get it
    back. By default, the hotkey is "control alt help".

@endnode

@node "Quit"
@toc "Menu"
@next "OptLoad"
@prev "Verbergen"

    Quit

    Terminate CX.

@endnode

@node "About"
@toc "Menu"
@next "Verbergen"
@prev "OptSave"

    About

    Brings up a big requester, showing you some information
    about CX and my address where you can sent me a postcard
    of your hometown (or a teddybear, or a CD (audio or
    ROM), ...)

@endnode

